{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f924c1ae-7524-424c-8f9b-7b2d0d552d0f","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` has **native MTP integration**, so `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is **no longer needed**. The SDK automatically detects that your project uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (via `EnableMSTestRunner`) and routes through it.\n\nYou can simply remove that property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_018vGp192XESXHVYciVxfVRL","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Y5hCnHJ5U4DRNvHUUTZyNV","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-87de3eeb1ab542c68fe5da8a540ff97d/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-87de3eeb1ab542c68fe5da8a540ff97d/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"c71960ae-6a44-469a-9356-c5c9ac7c9951","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. This property was needed in .NET 9 and earlier to opt into MTP support via `dotnet test`. In .NET 10, MTP is the default test runner integration for `dotnet test`.\n\nSo the user can:\n\n\n1. Remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` since it's redundant in .NET 10\n2. Keep `EnableMSTestRunner` to ensure the MSTest runner builds the test project as an executable with MTP integration\n\nLet me update the configuration and walk through the changes.","outputTokens":551,"requestId":"702D:9F427:DB652D2:F1B29E8:69F2A937"},"id":"0308ba2d-f51c-42cd-9a7a-c3872ecddc30","timestamp":"2026-04-30T0